The characters you allow are `A-Z`, `a-z`, and `0-9`.  In a regular expression `\\w` matches those characters.  And `\\W` matches **any but** those characters.  So set the latter to your delimiter and see how it works.
```
Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
scan.useDelimiter(&quot;\\W+&quot;);
while (true) {
	System.out.println(scan.next());
}
```
Each group of characters returned from `scan.next()` should only contain your allowable characters.

